title: Passwords simply don't sync properly to iOS
content: I use Firefox (139.0.4 (aarch64)) on my Mac as my daily browser. I also use Firefox as my primarly browser on iOS (139.1 (56110)). My passwords simply don't keep synced between the two. I'm logged in to both using the same Mozilla account. Some passwords sometimes sync. But many are missing on iOS, and many that are there are out of date. I've done the usual like logging out and in again, I've tried forcing sync manually, passwords are set to sync on both devices. This has been going on for years now and I'm at the point where I'm going to have to switch browsers as I can't keep not having access to my passwords on my phone. Any ideas on how I can fix this? Thanks!

title: Facebook won't load
content:
For the past 2 days, Facebook won't load when I try to change my page to another (just switching between accounts). It acts like it is changing or loading, and then I just get nothing. I have done all of the things that are requested from clearing my cache, browsing data, restarting, etc. Nothing is working. I've attached a picture of my screen of I receive when I try to change pages - the big F. LOL Facebook on my phone works fine. I've tried also turning off my VPN and it doesn't load.

I've also had issues with my Xfinity email loading unless I turn off my VPN.

So what is going on?

title: migrating tabs
content: Recently I've noted that tabs on my browser move from where I had them all the way to the far right end of the tabs list, and it happens at random. There'll be times when I click on another tab while listening to music or a video on another only to find the tab I was listening to had moved when I go to click back on it. Without fail, I've found these tabs at the far right end of the set of tabs, and I need to know how to put a stop to this. It's inconvenient, and annoying in extreme. This has to be due to a recent update, because up til a couple months ago, this didn't happen at all. If there's a setting that I can change in about:config, I would like to know about it, because you can bet I'll disable this feature.
